Goal The Shakhtar Donetsk man is in high demand, but wants to wait until after next summer’s tournament before he chooses his next club. In-demand Shakhtar Donetsk midfielder Fred says he wants to wait until after the World Cup to decide his future. The Brazil international is subject of interest from both Manchester clubs, with United and City hoping to seal a deal for the 25-year-old. Though United were reported to be closing in on a deal to sign Fred before the World Cup, the midfielder would prefer to wait until after next month’s tournament in Russia to decide his next move.